{"html":"<p><img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-bot.png\" alt=\"Polkadot bot\" height=\"120\" width=\"115\"></p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"overview\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#overview\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Overview\n        </h1><p>The Polkadot Telegram Query Bot is a Telegram bot that queries and returns data to users from Polkadot and other Substrate-based chains. Users can interact with this by sending them command messages in private or group chats.</p>\n<p>Built as part of the <a href=\"https://github.com/Web3Foundation/build-polkadot/issues/1\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Build Polkadot bounty challenges</strong></a>, sponsored by the Web3 Foundation, under the <strong>Build Polkadot Challenge 2: User Tools</strong> category.</p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"repository\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#repository\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Repository\n        </h1><p><a href=\"https://github.com/ayobuenavista/polkadot-telegram-query-bot\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/ayobuenavista/polkadot-telegram-query-bot</a></p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"technologies-used\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#technologies-used\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Technologies Used\n        </h1><ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/telegraf/telegraf\" target=\"_blank\">Telegraf</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://polkadot.js.org/api/\" target=\"_blank\">polkadot.js</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n        <h1 id=\"deployed-test-version\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#deployed-test-version\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Deployed Test Version\n        </h1><p>A live version of the bot is running. Search for <a href=\"https://t.me/polkadot_query_bot\" target=\"_blank\">@polkadot_query_bot</a> in Telegram.</p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"launching-the-bot\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#launching-the-bot\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Launching the Bot\n        </h1>\n        <h2 id=\"setup\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#setup\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Setup\n        </h2><p>To launch your own instance of the bot:</p>\n<p>1) Clone the <code>polkadot-telegram-query-bot</code> repo.</p>\n<pre class='language-bash'><code>$ <span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone git@github.com:ayobuenavista/polkadot-telegram-query-bot.git</code></pre><p>2) Install the required NPM packages.</p>\n<pre class='language-bash'><code>$ <span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span></code></pre><p>3) Obtain a Telegram bot token using Telegram&#39;s <a href=\"https://t.me/botfather\" target=\"_blank\">BotFather</a>. You can find a detailed guide on that <a href=\"https://core.telegram.org/bots#6-botfather\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>4) Create an .env file in the root directory, containing your Telegram bot token. Note: Omit the <code>bot</code> prefix in the Telegram token.</p>\n<p>e.g.</p>\n<pre class='language-bash'><code><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">TELEGRAM_TOKEN</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>xxxxxxxxx:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxxx</code></pre><p>5) Edit the <code>node</code> URIs in <code>./src/config/default.json</code> to add in your node or node provider, or you can leave the current definitions as is. At the moment, only Polkadot and Kusama are supported.</p>\n\n        <h2 id=\"running\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#running\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Running\n        </h2><p>To run in development mode (restarts at every file change)</p>\n<pre class='language-bash'><code><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> run dev</code></pre><p>To run in production mode</p>\n<pre class='language-bash'><code><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> run start</code></pre><p>You should see something like:</p>\n<p><img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-bot-start.png\" alt=\"Polkadot bot start\" height=\"250\" width=\"661\"></p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"bot-commands\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#bot-commands\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Bot Commands\n        </h1><p>Send the following commands directly to the bot or in a group where the bot is present.</p>\n<p>Note: if no chain is passed, Polkadot queried as default.</p>\n\n        <h2 id=\"balance\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#balance\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /balance\n        </h2><p>Returns the balance of an account</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/balance &lt;accountId&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"blockinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#blockinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /blockInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns the block info at the provided height</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/blockInfo &lt;height&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"chaininfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#chaininfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /chainInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns basic information of the Substrate chain</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/chainInfo &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"councilinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#councilinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /councilInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns council information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/councilInfo &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"democracyinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#democracyinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /democracyInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns democracy information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/democracyInfo &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"electionsinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#electionsinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /electionsInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns elections information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/electionsInfo &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"intentioncount\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#intentioncount\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /intentionCount\n        </h2><p>Returns the number of validators waiting to validate</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/intentionCount &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"intentions\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#intentions\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /intentions\n        </h2><p>Returns a range of validators that indicate their intention to validate (e.g. range: 0-10)</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/intentions &lt;range&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"latestblock\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#latestblock\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /latestBlock\n        </h2><p>Returns the latest block information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/latestBlock &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"proposalinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#proposalinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /proposalInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns the information of a proposal by providing the proposal hash</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/proposalInfo &lt;hash&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"proposals\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#proposals\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /proposals\n        </h2><p>Returns the list of proposals</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/proposals &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"runtimeconstants\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#runtimeconstants\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /runtimeConstants\n        </h2><p>Returns the runtime constant values</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/runtimeConstants &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"stakinginfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#stakinginfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /stakingInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns the staking information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/stakingInfo &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"sudokey\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#sudokey\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /sudoKey\n        </h2><p>Returns the sudo key accountId</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/sudoKey &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"techcomm\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#techcomm\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /techComm\n        </h2><p>Returns the technical committee information</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/techComm &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"techcommproposalinfo\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#techcommproposalinfo\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /techCommProposalInfo\n        </h2><p>Returns the information of a technical committee proposal by providing the proposal hash</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/techCommProposalInfo &lt;hash&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"techcommproposals\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#techcommproposals\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /techCommProposals\n        </h2><p>Returns the list of technical committee proposals</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/techCommProposals &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"validatorcount\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#validatorcount\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /validatorCount\n        </h2><p>Returns the number of active validators</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/validatorCount &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h2 id=\"validators\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#validators\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          /validators\n        </h2><p>Returns a range of active validators (e.g. range: 0-10)</p>\n<pre class='language-'><code>/validators &lt;range&gt; &lt;optional: chain&gt;</code></pre>\n        <h1 id=\"examples\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#examples\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Examples\n        </h1><p>To get balance information of an account:\n<img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-examples-balance.png\" alt=\"Polkadot /balance example\"></p>\n<p>To get the first 5 active validators in Kusama:\n<img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-examples-validators.png\" alt=\"Polkadot /validators example\"></p>\n<p>Get the chain information in Polkadot:\n<img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-examples-chaininfo.png\" alt=\"Polkadot /councilInfo example\"></p>\n<p>Get the council information in Kusama:\n<img src=\"articles/images/polkadot-examples-councilinfo.png\" alt=\"Polkadot /councilInfo example\"></p>\n\n        <h1 id=\"other-notes\" class=\"relative\">\n          <a\n            href=\"playground/polkadot/Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot#other-notes\"\n            class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\n          >\n            <span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\n          </a>\n          Other Notes\n        </h1><p>It was difficult to find a list of public node providers. Thankfully, <a href=\"https://polkadot.js.org/apps\" target=\"_blank\">https://polkadot.js.org/apps</a> returns a list of public node endpoints in the <code>node selection</code> screen. When clicking <code>custom endpoint</code>, you can see the WebSocket URI of the currently selected endpoint.</p>\n","deeplinks":[{"content":"Overview","slug":"overview","lvl":1,"i":0,"seen":0},{"content":"Repository","slug":"repository","lvl":1,"i":1,"seen":0},{"content":"Technologies Used","slug":"technologies-used","lvl":1,"i":2,"seen":0},{"content":"Deployed Test Version","slug":"deployed-test-version","lvl":1,"i":3,"seen":0},{"content":"Launching the Bot","slug":"launching-the-bot","lvl":1,"i":4,"seen":0},{"content":"Setup","slug":"setup","lvl":2,"i":5,"seen":0},{"content":"Running","slug":"running","lvl":2,"i":6,"seen":0},{"content":"Bot Commands","slug":"bot-commands","lvl":1,"i":7,"seen":0},{"content":"/balance","slug":"balance","lvl":2,"i":8,"seen":0},{"content":"/blockInfo","slug":"blockinfo","lvl":2,"i":9,"seen":0},{"content":"/chainInfo","slug":"chaininfo","lvl":2,"i":10,"seen":0},{"content":"/councilInfo","slug":"councilinfo","lvl":2,"i":11,"seen":0},{"content":"/democracyInfo","slug":"democracyinfo","lvl":2,"i":12,"seen":0},{"content":"/electionsInfo","slug":"electionsinfo","lvl":2,"i":13,"seen":0},{"content":"/intentionCount","slug":"intentioncount","lvl":2,"i":14,"seen":0},{"content":"/intentions","slug":"intentions","lvl":2,"i":15,"seen":0},{"content":"/latestBlock","slug":"latestblock","lvl":2,"i":16,"seen":0},{"content":"/proposalInfo","slug":"proposalinfo","lvl":2,"i":17,"seen":0},{"content":"/proposals","slug":"proposals","lvl":2,"i":18,"seen":0},{"content":"/runtimeConstants","slug":"runtimeconstants","lvl":2,"i":19,"seen":0},{"content":"/stakingInfo","slug":"stakinginfo","lvl":2,"i":20,"seen":0},{"content":"/sudoKey","slug":"sudokey","lvl":2,"i":21,"seen":0},{"content":"/techComm","slug":"techcomm","lvl":2,"i":22,"seen":0},{"content":"/techCommProposalInfo","slug":"techcommproposalinfo","lvl":2,"i":23,"seen":0},{"content":"/techCommProposals","slug":"techcommproposals","lvl":2,"i":24,"seen":0},{"content":"/validatorCount","slug":"validatorcount","lvl":2,"i":25,"seen":0},{"content":"/validators","slug":"validators","lvl":2,"i":26,"seen":0},{"content":"Examples","slug":"examples","lvl":1,"i":27,"seen":0},{"content":"Other Notes","slug":"other-notes","lvl":1,"i":28,"seen":0}],"metadata":{"id":"Polkadot-TelegramQueryBot","type":"project","title":"Polkadot Telegram Query Bot","description":"Telegram bot that queries data from Polkadot other Substrate-based chains","date":"17 Jun 2020"}}